Merge pull request #65 from wisdomlabs/master

mountable Express.js 4.x middleware

In app.js, set mount path to '/' by default.
Upgrade consolidate to fix cache error in production (https://github.com/tj/consolidate.js/pull/134).
Don't bother with a `config.site.baseUrl` configuration parameter. Instead, set up the `baseHref` local attribute on the response object such that it ensures a trailing slash.
Put a default favicon in place (needed for Express 4).
Minor tweaks to remove warnings from upgrade to Express 4.
Have the 'main' part of the module for npm point to the middleware. This way, when mongo-express is required within other modules, the middleware can be mounted.

Use `req.app.mountpath` instead of `config.site.baseUrl` for constructing routes.
Set up method-override to use POST body parameters.
Update README to explain how to use as Express 4 middleware.
Make sure the baseUrl gets propagated throughout the middleware.

Upgrade to Express 4 routing style with mountable middleware app.
Instead of `require('./config')` everywhere, pass the configuration through.
